<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-13T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-13T23:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1130: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-14T12:00:00+08:00">May 14,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 14—9:05
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to my telegram of May 9, 3 p.m. I am glad to be able to report
                            that I have just received a telegram dated May 10 through Hong Kong from
                            General Huang Shao-hung promising an armed guard to escort the American
                            missionaries out of Kweihsien. Department and Legation informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>